<figureCitation box="[958,1045,1940,1966]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1653,1677]" captionTargetBox="[162,1431,601,1625]" captionTargetId="figure-206@3.[151,1436,597,1630]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Diagnostic features of Hexarhopalus (H.) liuyixiaoi sp. nov. (A–G. Male; H–I. Female). A. Head and pronotum, in dorsal view; B. Antenna; C. Aedeagus, ventral view; D. Same, lateral view; E. Same, dorsal view; F. Abdominal ventrite VIII of male; G. Spiculum gastrale; H. Ventrite VIII of female and spiculum; I. Ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4440922" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4440922/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="280">Fig. 2H</figureCitation>
